      "message": "build: replace const char* exceptions with std::runtime_error\n\nFixes MinGW/libc++ test failures where `BOOST_CHECK_EXCEPTION` with `const char*` exceptions failed due to platform-specific exception handling differences.\n\nFollowing C++ Core Guidelines E.15 \"Throw by value, catch exceptions from a hierarchy by reference\", throw std::runtime_error instead of string literals.\nArray-to-pointer conversion makes string literal exceptions particularly fragile across platforms.\nAlso deleted HasReason::operator()(const char*) to prevent future use of raw string literal exceptions.\n\nCo-authored-by: Hennadii Stepanov <32963518+hebasto@users.noreply.github.com>",
